[1] Global (Pakistan, Nigeria, Angola, Myanmar) - GPEI
Date: Wed 25 Sep 2019
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative / WHO [edited]
http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/this-week/


Poliomyelitis update, 25 Sep 2019, WHO
---------------------------------
New wild poliovirus cases isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 4
Environment: 8

Total number of wild poliovirus cases in 2019: 82
Total number of wild poliovirus cases in 2018: 33

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 6
Environment: 2
Others: 9

Total number of cVDPV cases (all types) in 2019: 86
Total number of cVDPV cases (all types) in 2018: 104

Headlines
- The Global Polio Eradication Initiative and the Pakistan Polio Programme are looking for innovative ways to help quickly detect, control, and/or respond to the spread of anti-vaccination propaganda on social media in an urban population.

Summary of new viruses this week:
- Afghanistan: 1 wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1)- positive environmental sample;
- Pakistan: 4 WPV1 cases and 7 WPV1-positive environmental samples;
- Nigeria: 1 circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2)- positive case [environmental sample?];
- Angola - 4 cVDPV2 cases;
- Myanmar - 2 cVDPV1 cases.

Afghanistan
- No wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) case was reported. There are 16 WPV1 cases reported in 2019. There were 21 WPV1 cases reported in 2018.
- 1 WPV1-positive environmental sample was reported in the past week from Lashkargah district, Hilmand province. The sample was collected on [29 Aug 2019].

Pakistan
- 4 wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) cases were reported: 3 from Lakki Marwat district and 1 from Torghar district, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province. The onsets of paralysis were on [18, 24, 28, and 2 Aug 2019], respectively. There are 66 WPV1 cases reported in 2019. There were 12 WPV1 cases reported in 2018.
- 7 WPV1-positive environmental samples were reported: 2 each from Quetta and Killa Abdullah districts, and 1 from Pishin district, Balochistan province; and, 1 each from Faisalabad and Lahore districts, Punjab province. The samples were collected between [28 Aug 2019 - 5 Sep 2019].

Nigeria
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 16 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2019. There were 34 cVDPV2 cases in 2018.
- 1 cVDPV2-positive environmental sample was reported from Ilorin East LGA, Kwara state. The sample was collected on [27 Aug 2019].

Lake Chad
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week.
- In the Lake Chad region, cVDPV2 linked to the outbreak originating in Nigeria has been detected in Niger (1 case in 2019 and 10 cases in 2018 and in Cameroon (1 positive environmental sample, collected on [20 Apr 2019] in Extreme Nord)).
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across the Lake Chad subregion remains high.

Benin
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There is 1 cVDPV2 case in 2019 linked to Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across West Africa remains high.

Ghana
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There is 1 cVDPV2 case in 2019 linked to Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria
- Surveillance is being strengthened in neighbouring Togo, Cote d'Ivoire and Burkina Faso.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across West Africa remains high.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DR Congo)
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported. DRC is currently affected by 9 separate cVDPV2 outbreaks: 1 each originated in Haut Katanga, Mongala, Sankuru, Tanganika, Tshuapa, Kasai, and Kasai Central and 2 in Haut Lomami provinces.

Angola
- 4 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported this week: 1 from Tchikala-Tcholohan district, Huambo province; 1 from Cassongue district, Kwanza Sul province; 1 from Katchiungo district, Huambo province; and 1 from Quimbele district, Uige province. The onsets of paralysis were between [31 Jul 2019 and 15 Aug 2019]. There is a total of 19 cVDPV2 cases from 6 outbreaks reported in 2019.

Central African Republic:
- No case of cVDPV2 was reported this week. There are 6 reported cases in 2019 from 5 different outbreaks of cVDPV2 in 2019. Additional confirmed cVDPV2 community contact have been reported in CAR.
- No cVDPV2-positive environmental sample was reported.

Horn of Africa
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2019.
- Somalia has reported a total of 15 cVDPV cases (8 type 2, 6 type 3, and 1 coinfection of both type 2 and type 3) since the beginning of the outbreaks. The most recent cVDPV3 virus was from an AFP case from Runingod district, Middle Shabelle province, with an onset date of paralysis on [7 Sep 2018]. Circulating VDPV2 has also been detected during 2018 in 1 environmental sample in Kenya collected on [21 Mar 2018]. There are also 2 reported cases of cVDPV2 in Ethiopia, linked to Somalia in 2019.

Papua New Guinea
- No new cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) were reported this week. There were 26 cases reported in 2018.

Mozambique
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was been reported this week. There was 1 case reported in 2018.

Indonesia
- No circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) cases were reported this week. One cVDPV1 case was reported in 2018 from Papua province with onset of paralysis on [28 Nov 2018].
- This outbreak is not linked to the cVDPV1 in neighbouring Papua New Guinea.

Iran
- No new WPV1-positive environmental samples were reported this week. In total, 3 WPV1-positive environmental samples have been reported in 2019, all from Sistan and Balochistan province. The isolated viruses have been detected in environmental samples only, and genetic sequencing confirms they are linked to WPV1 circulating in Karachi, Pakistan.

China
- No cVDPV2 cases were reported this week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases in the country remains 1.

Myanmar
- 2 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) were reported this week from Papun district, Kayin province. The onsets of paralysis were on [8 and 29 Aug 2019]. There are 6 reported cases of cVDPV1 in 2019.

Philippines
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVPDV2) was reported this week. Two cVDPV2-positive environmental samples have been reported in 2019, and 2 VDPV2 AFP cases are under investigation.
- The Department of Health and local government units, with support from the World Health Organization (WHO) and UNICEF, are currently investigating the case.

Officially reported wild poliovirus cases as of 24 Sep 2019
Total global cases in 2019: 82 (compared with 18 for the same period in 2018)
- Total in endemic countries in 2019: 82 (compared with 18 for the same period in 2018)
- Total in non-endemic countries in 2019: 0 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018)

- Afghanistan: 16 cases in 2019 (compared with 14 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 2 Aug 2019
- Pakistan: 66 cases in 2019 (compared with 4 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 28 Aug 2019
- Nigeria: 0 cases in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 21 Aug 2016

Total global WPV1 cases in 2019: 82
Total global WPV1 cases in 2018: 33

Officially reported cVDPV cases as of 24 Sep 2019
- Angola: 19 cases in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 15 Aug 2019
- Benin: 1 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 30 Jun 2019
- Central African Republic: 6 cases in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 30 Jul 2019
- China: 1 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 25 Apr 2019
- Democratic Republic of the Congo: 30 cases in 2019 (compared with 15 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 26 Jul 2019
- Ethiopia: 2 cases in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 22 Jul 2019
- Ghana: 1 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 23 Jul 2019
- Indonesia (type 1): 0 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 27 Nov 2018
- Mozambique: 0 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 21 Oct 2018
- Myanmar (type 1): 6 cases in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 31 Aug 2019
- Niger: 1 case in 2019 (compared with 2 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 3 Apr 2019
- Nigeria: 16 cases in 2019 (compared with 11 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 8 Aug 2019
- Papua New Guinea (type 1): 0 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 18 Oct 2018
- Somalia (type 2): 3 cases in 2019 (compared with 5 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 8 May 2019
- Somalia (type 3): 0 case in 2019 (compared with 6 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 7 Sep 2018

Total global cVDPV cases in 2019: 86
Total global cVDPV cases in 2018: 104

